happens for most people

00:13:00.150 --> 00:13:02.870 align:middle line:84%
when they have a novel
or a new experience,

00:13:02.870 --> 00:13:05.510 align:middle line:84%
they repeat that experience
over in their mind again.

00:13:05.510 --> 00:13:08.000 align:middle line:90%
It's a natural propensity.

00:13:08.000 --> 00:13:10.370 align:middle line:84%
And the reason we do that
is because if we can fire

00:13:10.370 --> 00:13:12.680 align:middle line:84%
those circuits over
and over again,

00:13:12.680 --> 00:13:16.550 align:middle line:84%
by the act of repetition,
we can remember them.

00:13:16.550 --> 00:13:18.470 align:middle line:90%
So we learn from an experience.

00:13:18.470 --> 00:13:20.990 align:middle line:84%
Learning is making
new connections.

00:13:20.990 --> 00:13:23.550 align:middle line:84%
Remembering is maintaining
those connections.

00:13:23.550 --> 00:13:27.350 align:middle line:84%
And so there's a natural order
in which we review something

00:13:27.350 --> 00:13:29.810 align:middle line:90%
in order to remember it.

00:13:29.810 --> 00:13:32.540 align:middle line:84%
Now, the problem is,
with most people,

00:13:32.540 --> 00:13:36.710 align:middle line:84%
is that they become so
immersed in the feelings

00:13:36.710 --> 00:13:39.470 align:middle line:84%
of certain experiences
